00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:15,210
   

392
00:31:50,060 --> 00:31:52,090
Be careful.

393
00:31:52,090 --> 00:31:56,300
When in Seoul, if you blink wrong,

394
00:31:56,300 --> 00:31:58,970
your nose gets stolen.

395
00:32:11,790 --> 00:32:14,240
Gangnam is this way.

396
00:32:39,590 --> 00:32:41,810
- Hello. 
 - Goodness.

397
00:32:41,810 --> 00:32:44,070
You are the Young Master's teacher.

398
00:32:44,070 --> 00:32:46,170
I am happy to see you in Seoul.

399
00:32:46,170 --> 00:32:50,010
Me, too. By the way, what brings you here?

400
00:32:50,570 --> 00:32:52,490
Is Ms. Ca inside?

401
00:32:52,490 --> 00:32:54,060
Ms. Ca?

402
00:32:54,060 --> 00:32:57,770
Oh, yes, yes. Come on in.

403
00:33:02,070 --> 00:33:03,740
Good to see you, Madam Yeoju.

404
00:33:03,740 --> 00:33:07,320
I've been eager to hear from Seongsan Village.

405
00:33:07,320 --> 00:33:10,510
So, what did the old man say?

406
00:33:11,630 --> 00:33:16,050
Master said he would allow the fashion show.

407
00:33:16,050 --> 00:33:18,520
Bravo!

408
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:21,490
But under one condition.

409
00:33:21,490 --> 00:33:23,010
Condition?

410
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:27,590
I wish I could allow it unconditionally,

411
00:33:27,590 --> 00:33:34,260
but I cannot make such a major decision alone without the villagers' agreement.

412
00:33:34,260 --> 00:33:39,280
The people here are suspicious of events they are unfamiliar with.

413
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:43,070
So, come in person and try to persuade them.

414
00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:46,670
If more than half of the village is open to the idea,

415
00:33:46,670 --> 00:33:49,660
the deal will go through.

416
00:33:50,510 --> 00:33:56,850
To have the fashion show, come to the village and persuade the villagers?

417
00:33:56,850 --> 00:33:58,750
Just one moment.

418
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,400
A key?

419
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:10,120
I prepared a place for you to stay in the village.

420
00:34:19,810 --> 00:34:21,590
Is she shooting a period drama?

421
00:34:21,590 --> 00:34:23,210
Look at her hair. She's the real deal.

422
00:34:23,210 --> 00:34:25,340
It's so funny.

423
00:34:25,340 --> 00:34:28,010
What's she doing here?

424
00:34:28,890 --> 00:34:30,320
It's crazy.

425
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:33,510
Why are you spacing out like that?

426
00:34:33,510 --> 00:34:36,270
Are you sleeping with your eyes open?

427
00:34:36,270 --> 00:34:40,650
I was going to make a bed and lie down here if you came a bit later.

428
00:34:41,450 --> 00:34:43,610
Let us go.

429
00:34:43,610 --> 00:34:46,900
Before we go, let's stop by somewhere.

430
00:34:46,900 --> 00:34:48,650
We still have some time for the bus.

431
00:34:48,650 --> 00:34:50,280
Where are we stopping by?

432
00:34:50,280 --> 00:34:53,590
I need to make dinner for Master.

433
00:34:55,960 --> 00:34:59,510
It is my fault for not knowing how to get around in Seoul.

434
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:01,900
I suppose I will follow him.

435
00:35:06,730 --> 00:35:09,220
I brought the stuff you'd need.

436
00:35:09,220 --> 00:35:10,860
Are you really sure about this?

437
00:35:10,860 --> 00:35:13,250
Would it be colder than Seoul there?

438
00:35:14,300 --> 00:35:17,460
I need to care for myself there, too. Right?

439
00:35:17,460 --> 00:35:18,990
All right...

440
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:24,210
Hold on. What if I get bored?

441
00:35:24,210 --> 00:35:28,050
That's what I'm saying. You don't have the internet there, either.

442
00:35:28,050 --> 00:35:30,260
What? No internet?

443
00:35:30,260 --> 00:35:32,180
Yes.

444
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,810
I'll need to pick up some books on the way.

445
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:39,160
You know I hate being bored.

446
00:35:40,940 --> 00:35:42,450
How will you cook there?

447
00:35:42,450 --> 00:35:44,920
You probably can't get food delivered from outside.

448
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:49,560
Food? I almost forgot about food.

449
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:52,520
You know the instant rice? The stuff you put in the microwave.

450
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:54,790
I need to pick up some of that.

451
00:35:55,820 --> 00:35:58,660
Do they even have a microwave?

452
00:35:58,660 --> 00:36:00,780
Do I need to bring that, too?

453
00:36:03,050 --> 00:36:05,250
Are you worried I won't adjust?

454
00:36:05,250 --> 00:36:07,810
How could I not worry, then?

455
00:36:07,810 --> 00:36:09,880
I'm Camille.

456
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:14,010
If I can't adjust, I'll make them adjust to me.

457
00:36:31,110 --> 00:36:32,840
Let's see.

458
00:36:36,980 --> 00:36:40,710
Looks like cool tones look good on you.

459
00:36:40,710 --> 00:36:42,160
What are you saying?

460
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:43,730
Try this on.

461
00:36:43,730 --> 00:36:45,200
You want me to wear it?

462
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:47,590
The hanbok makes you stand out too much.

463
00:36:47,590 --> 00:36:51,540
Everyone was looking at you when you were walking in Gangnam.

464
00:36:52,780 --> 00:36:54,560
That's just what I thought.

465
00:36:55,990 --> 00:36:58,380
Seriously, why...

466
00:36:58,380 --> 00:37:00,040
Try it on.

467
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:35,600
What do you think?

468
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:39,620
Do you not notice me as much with this on?

469
00:37:40,610 --> 00:37:44,580
You said I was all you could see.

470
00:37:44,580 --> 00:37:48,880
Maybe you're more noticeable now.

471
00:37:51,090 --> 00:37:53,310
I'll take those.

472
00:37:54,320 --> 00:37:57,720
- Enjoy. 
 - Gosh.

473
00:37:57,720 --> 00:38:01,250
Is this what I saw on YouTube—

474
00:38:01,250 --> 00:38:04,650
This is called tonkatsu.

475
00:38:04,650 --> 00:38:10,000
It's what sophisticated people in Seoul eat.

476
00:38:12,100 --> 00:38:16,270
Okay. Using a fork and knife is important in Western cuisine.

477
00:38:16,270 --> 00:38:18,170
Using the fork...

478
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:21,840
pierce it and...

479
00:38:21,840 --> 00:38:26,790
saw back and forth. Back and forth.

480
00:38:26,790 --> 00:38:29,250
Back and forth.

481
00:38:44,090 --> 00:38:47,780
Gosh, what is the deal...

482
00:39:12,610 --> 00:39:14,360
Eat slowly.

483
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:16,200
You'll get an upset stomach.

484
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,140
When I get more money later,

485
00:39:29,140 --> 00:39:32,140
I'll get you one with cheese in it.

486
00:40:05,450 --> 00:40:07,360
Should we go there?

487
00:40:36,210 --> 00:40:39,700
Is this your second wish, Teacher?

488
00:40:39,700 --> 00:40:41,250
No.

489
00:40:42,940 --> 00:40:45,670
Draw me right here.

490
00:40:45,670 --> 00:40:47,370
P-Pardon?

491
00:40:47,370 --> 00:40:49,000
Hold on.

492
00:40:52,030 --> 00:40:53,610
Here.

493
00:41:24,720 --> 00:41:28,720
♫  A midday dream in plenty of sunlight  ♫

494
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:32,710
♫  I'm starting to miss you  ♫

495
00:41:32,710 --> 00:41:40,710
♫  I follow the wind and look for you  ♫

496
00:41:40,710 --> 00:41:44,740
♫  When the stars show up in the dark sky  ♫

497
00:41:44,740 --> 00:41:49,790
♫  It was so very beautiful  ♫

498
00:41:49,790 --> 00:41:56,810
♫  I've been picturing you in the night sky  ♫

499
